President Barack Obama has sent a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency declared in response to the September 11, 2001 terrorist attacks will continue for an additional year. The President cited the ongoing terrorist threat as the reason for the extension. This notice is in accordance with Section 202(d) of the National Emergencies Act, which requires the President to publish a notice in the Federal Register and transmit it to Congress prior to the anniversary date of the emergency declaration in order to continue the emergency.